An input directory has the following structure:


├── raw_inputs_all
   	├── movie_1										<- size N*N*N*Nframes
   	├── movie_2
	├── movie_3
	...

├── preprocessed_inputs_all
   └── res_128x128_filters_sf3o3s2 					<- specific preprocessing pipeline
		── stimset_metadata.yaml					<- Common metadata of the preprocessed input movies
	   	├── input_movie_1							<- size Nnet*Nnet*Nfilters*Nframes
	   	├── input_movie_2
		├── input_movie_3
	...


├── raw_inputs_sets
    └── stimset1_raw
        ├── movie_1									<- symlink to raw_inputs_all/movie_1
        └── movie_2


├── preprocessed_inputs_sets
│   └── stimset1_prepro_res_128x128_filters_sf3o3s2
│       ├── input_movie_1							< symlink to preprocessed_inputs_all/input_movie_1
│       ├── input_movie_2
│       └── stimset_metadata.yaml					<- same metadata as in preprocessed_inputs_all
	...


└── session_stims									<- specific sequences of input movies
	└── 'stimset1_prepro_res_128x128_filters_
			sf3o3s2___50picks'						<- pseudorandom list of file paths pertaining to a given
														preprocessed stimulus set.
													   A session points to one of those files.
													   path names are relative to $INPUTDIR
